pageTitle: High School Sports | Sept. 3 2010 football Lehi-Hillcrest | Deseret News
textBeforeTable: Rushing Individual stats Tanner Kemp had three touchdowns two rushing and one 16-yard completion to Brock Whitworth to lead Hillcrest. Kemp was 15-for-21 for 164 yards in the air and rushed for 108 yards in the win. Safeties B.J. Edman and Kalob Kirmer also shored up the defense for the Huskies.
